translated: Eländer, Olof Bertil Eberhard, church assistant and curate. Born December 11, 1910 in Gothenburg to editor Elis E. and Hilma Jansson. He graduated from Gothenburg High Latin School in 1930, received a degree in theology and philosophy in Gothenburg in 1931, a degree in theology from Lund University in 1938, and passed his practical theology examination and was ordained as a priest in Skara Diocese the same year. After various appointments, including in Hjälistad, Borås Caroli, and Amnehärad, he became a church assistant and curate in Grästorp in 1946. He married in the year 19xx.
